While the Nigerian government is still battling with the spread of coronavirus in the country, the deadly disease has started killing in the country. Report indicated that Nigeria recorded the first death from coronavirus in a case is a 67 years old man who returned from the United Kingdom (UK) after medical treatment.
The report indicated the deceased had underlying medical conditions which include multiple myeloma and diabetes and was undergoing chemotherapy.
However, further details were not unfolded but it is apposite that the government and agencies do more sensitization on the global pandemic that has grounded the world from Europe to America, Asia, the Caribbean and Africa.
The Italian President has given up on government intervention efforts, surrendering to divine intervention to save Italy which has recorded uncontrolled high death rate.

			
